df_cell6 = df.take(idx.repeat(factor)).reset_index(drop=True)

df.head(3)

Reason: Concatenating 50 copies of the DataFrame allocates and merges 50 separate tables, which is expensive even on the GPU. By repeating the row indices once (idx.repeat) and then performing a single take (gather) on the GPU, we avoid the multi-copy concat overhead and leverage a single efficient gather kernel. The final reset_index restores a 0..N−1 index.
